1
00:00:49,560 --> 00:00:50,200
Xu Xiao,

2
00:00:51,160 --> 00:00:52,690
who are you teaming up with?

3
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:55,120
Teacher.

4
00:00:58,600 --> 00:00:58,960
I...

5
00:00:59,560 --> 00:01:01,160
I want to team up with Xu Xiao.

6
00:01:04,959 --> 00:01:05,680
Speak up.

7
00:01:06,080 --> 00:01:08,080
I want to team up with Xu Xiao.

8
00:01:10,280 --> 00:01:10,800
Xu Xiao,

9
00:01:11,520 --> 00:01:12,520
what do you think?

10
00:01:13,680 --> 00:01:15,560
Okay, we will follow these groups

11
00:01:15,560 --> 00:01:17,620
and start the next round of learning.

12
00:01:22,760 --> 00:01:23,560
Zhao Xiaocen.

13
00:01:25,640 --> 00:01:27,360
I couldn't tell you were so two-faced.

14
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:28,960
Didn't we agree during our last meal

15
00:01:28,960 --> 00:01:30,960
to let Lin Yuexin team up with Xu Xiao?

16
00:01:30,960 --> 00:01:32,200
What was wrong with you this morning?

17
00:01:32,200 --> 00:01:33,240
Jumping out so impatiently,

18
00:01:33,240 --> 00:01:34,320
playing such a passive-aggressive game.

19
00:01:34,320 --> 00:01:34,920
No.

20
00:01:35,960 --> 00:01:37,840
It's because I was too anxious.

21
00:01:38,080 --> 00:01:39,240
What are you anxious about?

22
00:01:39,240 --> 00:01:40,520
Afraid someone will take your place?

23
00:01:40,520 --> 00:01:41,880
It's because Xu Xiao...

24
00:01:42,640 --> 00:01:43,560
Right here.

25
00:01:44,240 --> 00:01:44,759
Coming.

26
00:01:46,039 --> 00:01:46,720
I'm sorry.

27
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:48,720
I don't even know what to say.

28
00:01:49,640 --> 00:01:51,700
You're not even pretending anymore.

29
00:01:51,880 --> 00:01:53,120
Yan Xue, don't be mad.

30
00:01:53,560 --> 00:01:54,960
I'll apologize to Yuexin later.

31
00:01:54,960 --> 00:01:56,289
Who needs your apology?

32
00:01:56,880 --> 00:01:57,560
Yan Xue,

33
00:01:58,680 --> 00:02:00,010
what are you doing here?

34
00:02:01,160 --> 00:02:03,090
I don't know what I'm doing either.

35
00:02:03,120 --> 00:02:03,800
Yan Xue!

36
00:02:07,720 --> 00:02:08,250
Let's go.

37
00:02:18,320 --> 00:02:19,120
What's wrong?

38
00:02:19,440 --> 00:02:19,970
Nothing.

39
00:02:23,120 --> 00:02:24,520
Wu Jing, didn't you want to go shopping?

40
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:25,240
I'll go with you.

41
00:02:25,240 --> 00:02:26,120
I don't want to.

42
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:27,560
Yes, you do. Let's go.

43
00:02:27,680 --> 00:02:29,610
I promised to go with you last time.

44
00:02:30,640 --> 00:02:32,800
Yan Xue, it's just teaming up.

45
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:35,260
Don't talk about Xiaocen like that anymore.

46
00:02:36,280 --> 00:02:37,040
No.

47
00:02:37,280 --> 00:02:38,280
What do you mean?

48
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:40,560
Now you're making it seem like I'm bullying her.

49
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:41,720
No, I didn't.

50
00:02:41,720 --> 00:02:42,440
Yuexin,

51
00:02:42,600 --> 00:02:43,680
what makes me angry is that

52
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:45,360
we treated Zhao Xiaocen as a friend,

53
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:46,800
but she's two-faced.

54
00:02:47,240 --> 00:02:48,360
Didn't she say at dinner that day

55
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:49,480
she didn't like Xu Xiao?

56
00:02:49,480 --> 00:02:50,560
Didn't you tell me last time

57
00:02:50,560 --> 00:02:52,120
that you were interested in Xu Xiao?

58
00:02:52,120 --> 00:02:53,360
That's why I helped you.

59
00:02:53,360 --> 00:02:55,120
She also silently agreed to you teaming up with Xu Xiao.

60
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:57,480
But now you're taking her side and blaming me.

61
00:02:57,480 --> 00:02:59,010
Shouldn't I be speechless?

62
00:02:59,120 --> 00:03:00,280
Yan Xue, don't be mad.

63
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:01,600
I know you mean well,

64
00:03:02,120 --> 00:03:03,580
but Xiao Cen meant no harm.

65
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:06,560
No, I'm not mad at you.

66
00:03:06,560 --> 00:03:08,400
I just think you're too kind.

67
00:03:08,440 --> 00:03:09,760
You're too much of a pushover.

68
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:11,280
I just can't stand people taking advantage of you.

69
00:03:11,280 --> 00:03:12,610
That's why I helped you.

70
00:03:13,120 --> 00:03:14,080
Forget it, forget it.

71
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:15,160
You did nothing wrong.

72
00:03:15,160 --> 00:03:15,760
She did nothing wrong either.

73
00:03:15,760 --> 00:03:17,090
It's all my fault, okay?

74
00:03:17,320 --> 00:03:18,400
Let me calm down for a bit.

75
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:18,920
Let me calm down.

76
00:03:18,920 --> 00:03:19,280
No.

77
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:20,140
Leave me alone.

78
00:03:42,079 --> 00:03:42,880
Yuexin.

79
00:03:44,640 --> 00:03:45,400
I'm sorry.

80
00:03:46,480 --> 00:03:48,200
I didn't consider

81
00:03:48,920 --> 00:03:50,600
your feelings today.

82
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:53,560
I...

83
00:03:56,280 --> 00:03:58,040
It's not actually that

84
00:03:59,560 --> 00:04:00,960
I like Xu Xiao.

85
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:02,600
But rather...

86
00:04:06,600 --> 00:04:08,800
I just don't want him to ignore me

87
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:13,360
and lose a friend like him.

88
00:04:14,960 --> 00:04:16,200
Including you.

89
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:18,360
So,

90
00:04:20,399 --> 00:04:21,930
about what happened today.

91
00:04:23,960 --> 00:04:26,040
I was wrong. I'm sorry.

92
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:34,560
I just don't want everyone

93
00:04:34,560 --> 00:04:35,600
to hate me.

94
00:05:06,520 --> 00:05:07,280
Hello?

95
00:05:08,080 --> 00:05:09,340
Do you have time later?

96
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:11,560
Can we meet?

97
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:37,560
Xu Xiao.

98
00:05:39,920 --> 00:05:42,250
I still want to explain it to you in person.

99
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:44,360
I really wasn't following you then.

100
00:05:44,960 --> 00:05:47,400
It's because Xiaoxing said you were there,

101
00:05:47,400 --> 00:05:48,000
and then I...

102
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:48,640
I know.

103
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:53,860
I was in a bad mood that day too.

104
00:06:01,960 --> 00:06:03,520
Do you think there's anyone

105
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:04,960
who can create a kind of

106
00:06:04,960 --> 00:06:07,290
porcelain that makes people feel better?

107
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:10,000
Actually,

108
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:13,330
when you volunteered to team up today,

109
00:06:14,280 --> 00:06:15,540
I was quite surprised.

110
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:18,640
After all,

111
00:06:20,520 --> 00:06:22,250
my attitude towards you before

112
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:23,240
was so bad.

113
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:28,680
I...

114
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:30,480
I...

115
00:06:31,120 --> 00:06:33,360
I don't know what got into me today.

116
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:35,760
I just raised my hand.

117
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:39,240
Because I thought at the time

118
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:41,080
that only at work

119
00:06:41,080 --> 00:06:42,360
would you talk to me.

120
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:45,970
I didn't want it to be like that.

121
00:06:50,080 --> 00:06:52,560
Because since I came to Jingdezhen,

122
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:55,360
you were the first friend I made.

123
00:07:06,520 --> 00:07:07,280
First of all,

124
00:07:08,040 --> 00:07:10,300
I'm very grateful that you're my friend.

125
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:14,330
I haven't been in good health since I was a kid.

126
00:07:14,680 --> 00:07:16,600
So my schooling was on and off,

127
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:18,770
and I didn't make many friends.

128
00:07:19,640 --> 00:07:21,240
After I came to Jingdezhen,

129
00:07:21,840 --> 00:07:23,280
I was very worried that I would be all alone

130
00:07:23,280 --> 00:07:24,560
just like before.

131
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:28,960
So I really cherish our friendship.

132
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:32,200
But I don't seem to be good at

133
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:35,280
looking at things from others' perspectives.

134
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:36,920
Even today,

135
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:39,320
I did something wrong.

136
00:07:39,480 --> 00:07:40,040
No.

137
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:42,480
Xiaocen,

138
00:07:44,960 --> 00:07:45,960
you shouldn't always put the blame

139
00:07:45,960 --> 00:07:47,040
on yourself.

140
00:07:49,680 --> 00:07:51,940
Those who are willing to stay by your side

141
00:07:52,640 --> 00:07:54,200
will never leave you

142
00:07:55,480 --> 00:07:56,610
over a small matter.

143
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:01,200
Thank you.

144
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:05,640
All right.

145
00:08:06,680 --> 00:08:07,210
Let's go.

146
00:08:08,440 --> 00:08:10,370
We still owe Mr. Yue an assignment.

147
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:11,720
Okay.

148
00:08:14,360 --> 00:08:14,890
Let's go.

149
00:08:45,240 --> 00:08:45,720
Well...

150
00:08:48,920 --> 00:08:52,720
The man who tricked you into buying the fake porcelain shard that day

151
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:55,600
was my dad.

152
00:09:10,880 --> 00:09:13,360
This is our university's graduate school.

153
00:09:13,520 --> 00:09:15,320
It has a replica of an ancient wood-fired kiln

154
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:17,580
and supporting production facilities.

155
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:19,300
Come in, everyone.

156
00:09:20,800 --> 00:09:22,080
The production of ceramics

157
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:24,210
requires at least seventy-two steps,

158
00:09:24,520 --> 00:09:26,650
and sometimes hundreds of processes.

159
00:09:27,280 --> 00:09:29,080
Since our class time is limited,

160
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:30,200
this time

161
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:32,920
we will skip the preliminary steps including soil selection, grinding,

162
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:34,160
filtering, mixing,

163
00:09:34,160 --> 00:09:35,840
moistening, and kneading.

164
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:38,610
We will start directly with throwing.

165
00:10:13,160 --> 00:10:16,520
Now everyone's clay pieces are semi-dry,

166
00:10:16,640 --> 00:10:18,400
which is perfect for trimming.

167
00:10:18,680 --> 00:10:20,960
That means using the tools on hand

168
00:10:21,040 --> 00:10:22,840
to refine the piece,

169
00:10:22,960 --> 00:10:24,720
making its surface smooth

170
00:10:24,720 --> 00:10:26,050
and its thickness even.

171
00:10:27,840 --> 00:10:28,600
Look at this.

172
00:10:30,760 --> 00:10:32,800
Next is the painting stage.

173
00:10:33,520 --> 00:10:35,520
First, draw the pattern on the raw piece,

174
00:10:35,520 --> 00:10:37,250
then color it with a fine brush.

175
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:38,600
As for this stage,

176
00:10:38,920 --> 00:10:40,520
you're all familiar with it.

177
00:10:40,520 --> 00:10:43,600
We already learned this when making Yuan blue and white porcelain last time.

178
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:44,920
I hope everyone can

179
00:10:44,920 --> 00:10:46,400
do better this time.

180
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:03,160
All right.

181
00:11:03,520 --> 00:11:04,680
Seal the kiln now.

182
00:11:06,680 --> 00:11:07,280
Students.

183
00:11:08,160 --> 00:11:09,160
Firing a wood kiln

184
00:11:09,320 --> 00:11:12,720
requires three steps: filling, firing, and extinguishing.

185
00:11:13,080 --> 00:11:15,520
During the 30-hour firing process,

186
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:17,080
you need to know when to raise the temperature

187
00:11:17,080 --> 00:11:18,200
and when to maintain it.

188
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:19,320
When adding wood,

189
00:11:19,760 --> 00:11:21,690
the kiln master must stay close by.

190
00:11:21,960 --> 00:11:24,080
They need to continuously add wood

191
00:11:24,360 --> 00:11:27,090
and constantly monitor the kiln's temperature.

192
00:11:42,160 --> 00:11:43,240
Recently,

193
00:11:43,320 --> 00:11:44,980
under the guidance of Mr. Yue,

194
00:11:45,360 --> 00:11:47,960
we visited a traditional wood-fired kiln site

195
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:50,340
and learned how to make ceramics.

196
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:52,560
It turns out that just for glazing,

197
00:11:52,560 --> 00:11:54,490
there are many different methods.

198
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:56,600
There are many types of glazing,

199
00:11:57,320 --> 00:11:58,980
including the blowing method

200
00:11:59,320 --> 00:12:00,650
and the dipping method.

201
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:03,780
The pouring glaze method.

202
00:12:04,120 --> 00:12:06,400
After drying, it is placed in the kiln.

203
00:12:06,400 --> 00:12:08,680
Firing for up to 30 hours

204
00:12:09,080 --> 00:12:10,880
produces exquisite porcelain.

205
00:12:11,880 --> 00:12:13,360
Traditional ceramic making

206
00:12:13,360 --> 00:12:14,840
has 72 processes.

207
00:12:15,960 --> 00:12:17,560
Throwing.

208
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:21,280
Trimming.

209
00:12:24,840 --> 00:12:26,080
Painting.

210
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:30,960
Glazing.

211
00:12:36,160 --> 00:12:37,760
Overglaze painting.

212
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:43,960
Finally, after high-temperature firing,

213
00:12:44,680 --> 00:12:46,480
it becomes exquisite ceramics.

214
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:49,360
Every process is indispensable.

215
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:53,000
A journey of a thousand miles begins with a single step.

216
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:54,440
Life is the same.

217
00:12:59,280 --> 00:12:59,880
Class.

218
00:13:00,760 --> 00:13:03,040
This is Xu Xiao and Xiao Cen's work.

219
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:03,720
Not bad.

220
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:08,080
Yan Xue and Wu Jing's work is also good.

221
00:13:08,880 --> 00:13:11,080
This is Yuexin's work, which is also good.

222
00:13:11,080 --> 00:13:11,640
Class.

223
00:13:12,160 --> 00:13:13,290
From your homework,

224
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:15,960
I saw your clumsiness and nervousness,

225
00:13:16,720 --> 00:13:17,980
but more importantly,

226
00:13:18,560 --> 00:13:19,840
I saw your earnestness

227
00:13:20,120 --> 00:13:21,200
and your wisdom.

228
00:13:22,680 --> 00:13:23,400
Now,

229
00:13:23,680 --> 00:13:25,760
let me talk to you about it.

230
00:13:28,080 --> 00:13:29,000
I finally found you.

231
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:29,640
Who is this?

232
00:13:29,640 --> 00:13:30,200
Go.

233
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:31,200
Stop. What are you doing?

234
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:32,200
Come with me. Go, go.

235
00:13:32,200 --> 00:13:32,680
Let go.

236
00:13:32,680 --> 00:13:33,400
What are you doing?

237
00:13:33,400 --> 00:13:34,720
Let go. Let go.

238
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:35,240
Let go.

239
00:13:35,720 --> 00:13:36,240
Let go.

240
00:13:37,080 --> 00:13:37,720
This is a classroom.

241
00:13:37,720 --> 00:13:38,280
Okay.

242
00:13:38,280 --> 00:13:39,210
What do you want?

243
00:13:39,240 --> 00:13:40,040
Mr. Xu.

244
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:42,000
You have a backer now, right?

245
00:13:42,120 --> 00:13:43,280
You didn't answer the phone.

246
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:44,520
You didn't go to the antique shop.

247
00:13:44,520 --> 00:13:45,600
Are you feeling guilty?

248
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:46,730
Are you avoiding me?

249
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:48,320
You know you are talking nonsense,

250
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:49,760
and you can't take responsibility, right?

251
00:13:49,760 --> 00:13:50,640
Who is talking nonsense?

252
00:13:50,640 --> 00:13:51,160
You.

253
00:13:51,400 --> 00:13:53,000
Breaking in and making trouble like this,

254
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:55,160
it disrupts our normal teaching order.

255
00:13:55,160 --> 00:13:56,600
Please don't cause trouble here.

256
00:13:56,600 --> 00:13:58,000
He is your student, right?

257
00:13:58,000 --> 00:13:58,520
Yes.

258
00:13:58,720 --> 00:14:00,850
Can a student just talk nonsense here?

259
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:02,960
Your student

260
00:14:03,120 --> 00:14:04,360
said our item

261
00:14:04,520 --> 00:14:05,320
is fake.

262
00:14:05,480 --> 00:14:07,480
But I found a master appraiser

263
00:14:07,520 --> 00:14:08,200
to take a look.

264
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:08,960
It is real.

265
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:09,600
What now?

266
00:14:09,800 --> 00:14:11,280
Can you take responsibility for this?

267
00:14:11,280 --> 00:14:14,410
If you can't, the school will take full responsibility.

268
00:14:17,280 --> 00:14:18,040
Look.

269
00:14:18,520 --> 00:14:19,040
Look.

270
00:14:19,240 --> 00:14:20,320
Everyone, look carefully.

271
00:14:20,320 --> 00:14:21,280
Watch closely.

272
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:22,480
Teacher,

273
00:14:22,520 --> 00:14:23,400
you verify it.

274
00:14:23,640 --> 00:14:24,840
Verify it if you dare.

275
00:14:24,920 --> 00:14:26,320
Let's see if you tell the truth.

276
00:14:26,320 --> 00:14:26,850
Alright.

277
00:14:27,120 --> 00:14:27,640
You two,

278
00:14:28,680 --> 00:14:30,320
let's take this outside, shall we?

279
00:14:30,320 --> 00:14:31,520
No, we are staying right here.

280
00:14:31,520 --> 00:14:31,920
Right here.

281
00:14:31,920 --> 00:14:33,200
What? Afraid people will hear?

282
00:14:33,200 --> 00:14:34,640
Come on, everyone, judge for yourselves.

283
00:14:34,640 --> 00:14:35,300
Okay, okay.

284
00:14:36,040 --> 00:14:37,170
A couple of days ago.

285
00:14:37,240 --> 00:14:39,320
My dad took this blue-and-white porcelain bowl

286
00:14:39,320 --> 00:14:40,560
to an antique shop.

287
00:14:41,320 --> 00:14:43,200
It's the place where he works part-time.

288
00:14:43,200 --> 00:14:45,360
He said our stuff was fake.

289
00:14:45,520 --> 00:14:46,960
Is that true? Right?

290
00:14:46,960 --> 00:14:47,440
Yes.

291
00:14:47,440 --> 00:14:49,040
Just because of what he said,

292
00:14:49,320 --> 00:14:51,080
I smashed this porcelain bowl.

293
00:14:51,160 --> 00:14:53,020
Luckily, I was careful at the time

294
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:56,080
and brought back the bottom of my blue-and-white porcelain bowl.

295
00:14:56,080 --> 00:14:57,040
After going back,

296
00:14:57,040 --> 00:14:59,320
I was so angry that I couldn't even swallow.

297
00:14:59,320 --> 00:15:01,250
We found another appraisal agency

298
00:15:01,320 --> 00:15:04,200
and confirmed that it's a genuine piece from the Chenghua period.

299
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:05,080
Your

300
00:15:05,240 --> 00:15:05,600
dad.

301
00:15:06,040 --> 00:15:07,840
You almost ruined me.

302
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:08,640
Do you know that?

303
00:15:08,640 --> 00:15:09,880
How are you going to compensate?

304
00:15:09,880 --> 00:15:10,540
Okay, okay.

305
00:15:10,680 --> 00:15:12,140
Please calm down, you two.

306
00:15:12,840 --> 00:15:14,120
What about the other fragments?

307
00:15:14,120 --> 00:15:16,000
It's good enough that I could get this porcelain piece back.

308
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:17,800
The rest are nowhere to be found.

309
00:15:17,920 --> 00:15:18,280
Okay.

310
00:15:19,040 --> 00:15:20,320
Can I take a look?

311
00:15:38,600 --> 00:15:39,080
Xu Xiao.

312
00:15:40,920 --> 00:15:42,180
Did you look at it then?

313
00:15:42,480 --> 00:15:42,960
I did.

314
00:15:43,720 --> 00:15:44,920
But I didn't touch it.

315
00:15:45,440 --> 00:15:46,600
It's a fake at first glance.

316
00:15:46,600 --> 00:15:47,560
You little brat,

317
00:15:47,680 --> 00:15:48,240
you're still talking nonsense here!

318
00:15:48,240 --> 00:15:49,600
Stand back.

319
00:15:52,920 --> 00:15:53,720
Sir,

320
00:15:56,280 --> 00:15:57,120
this bottom

321
00:15:57,480 --> 00:15:58,800
looks authentic.

322
00:15:59,160 --> 00:15:59,720
But

323
00:16:01,680 --> 00:16:03,520
it could be grafted.

324
00:16:03,800 --> 00:16:04,330
Grafted?

325
00:16:04,400 --> 00:16:04,800
Yes.

326
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:07,060
In porcelain forgery,

327
00:16:07,120 --> 00:16:08,520
the most important thing

328
00:16:08,520 --> 00:16:11,000
is mixing old and new pieces.

329
00:16:11,080 --> 00:16:13,080
Using an old piece as a base,

330
00:16:13,120 --> 00:16:15,880
a newly fired piece is added on top.

331
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:17,120
At the seams,

332
00:16:17,120 --> 00:16:20,080
glaze is carefully applied to cover it up.

333
00:16:20,120 --> 00:16:21,920
This is highly deceptive.

334
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:23,160
Do you mean

335
00:16:24,160 --> 00:16:25,800
my old man got scammed?

336
00:16:25,840 --> 00:16:26,840
It's possible.

337
00:16:27,360 --> 00:16:29,040
You're just protecting your student

338
00:16:29,040 --> 00:16:30,700
and lying through your teeth.

339
00:16:30,920 --> 00:16:32,000
Please calm down.

340
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:34,520
Gentlemen,

341
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:36,280
we will find evidence

342
00:16:36,800 --> 00:16:38,800
and give you a satisfactory answer.

343
00:16:39,120 --> 00:16:39,680
Fine.

344
00:16:40,800 --> 00:16:42,240
A satisfactory answer?

345
00:16:45,280 --> 00:16:46,610
A satisfactory answer?

346
00:16:48,160 --> 00:16:49,200
A satisfactory answer?

347
00:16:49,200 --> 00:16:49,640
Dad!

348
00:16:51,480 --> 00:16:51,840
Dad!

349
00:16:51,960 --> 00:16:52,920
Answer?

350
00:16:54,160 --> 00:16:54,920
Answer?

351
00:16:55,320 --> 00:16:55,840
Answer?

352
00:16:55,840 --> 00:16:56,160
You...

353
00:16:56,160 --> 00:16:57,020
My assignment!

354
00:16:58,960 --> 00:16:59,840
Answer?

355
00:16:59,840 --> 00:17:00,320
What

356
00:17:00,720 --> 00:17:01,520
are you doing?

357
00:17:01,640 --> 00:17:02,280
What?

358
00:17:02,280 --> 00:17:04,079
Stop! Don't smash it!

359
00:17:04,079 --> 00:17:05,800
Stop! Don't smash it!

360
00:17:05,800 --> 00:17:06,760
Call the police!

361
00:17:10,480 --> 00:17:10,920
Dad,

362
00:17:12,240 --> 00:17:13,040
what's wrong?

363
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:13,640
Dad!

364
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:19,240
You!

365
00:17:20,040 --> 00:17:21,560
Because of your one word,

366
00:17:23,280 --> 00:17:24,680
300,000 is gone!

367
00:17:24,680 --> 00:17:25,560
300,000!

368
00:17:25,560 --> 00:17:25,920
Dad!

369
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:28,400
You have to give me an explanation for this!

370
00:17:28,400 --> 00:17:29,480
Dad!

371
00:17:29,520 --> 00:17:30,320
What's wrong?

372
00:17:31,080 --> 00:17:32,880
Hurry, take him to the hospital!

373
00:17:35,920 --> 00:17:36,960
Here's what happened.

374
00:17:36,960 --> 00:17:38,090
I was having a class.

375
00:17:38,280 --> 00:17:40,240
Today is the students' assignment exhibition,

376
00:17:40,240 --> 00:17:41,320
which is displayed right here.

377
00:17:41,320 --> 00:17:42,040
Then they

378
00:17:42,040 --> 00:17:43,640
suddenly broke in from here.

379
00:17:43,960 --> 00:17:46,400
This old man bought a piece of porcelain at a shop.

380
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:48,080
Xu Xiao said it might be fake.

381
00:17:48,520 --> 00:17:50,120
Now they came to find Xu Xiao.

382
00:17:50,160 --> 00:17:50,800
They got so excited,

383
00:17:50,800 --> 00:17:52,280
He smashed a classmate's assignment.

384
00:17:52,280 --> 00:17:55,340
Look, isn't there broken porcelain all over the floor?

385
00:18:07,480 --> 00:18:08,680
Strictly speaking,

386
00:18:09,440 --> 00:18:12,840
